[ Changelog ]

Version                Description
7.0.0   This function is now supported on Windows.

===============================================================================
[ Notes ]

  Note:

  On Windows getrusage() will only return the following members:

   + "ru_stime.tv_sec"
   + "ru_stime.tv_usec"
   + "ru_utime.tv_sec"
   + "ru_utime.tv_usec"
   + "ru_majflt" (only if {who} is RUSAGE_SELF)
   + "ru_maxrss" (only if {who} is RUSAGE_SELF)

  If getrusage() is called with {who} set to 1 (RUSAGE_CHILDREN), then resource
  usage for threads are collected (meaning that internally the function is
  called with RUSAGE_THREAD).

  Note:

  on BeOS 2000, only the following members are returned:

   + "ru_stime.tv_sec"
   + "ru_stime.tv_usec"
   + "ru_utime.tv_sec"
   + "ru_utime.tv_usec"

